        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>RED FLAG DRILL-DOWN:
When the user asks about red flags, failed requirements, deal blockers, or &quot;what can&apos;t we meet?&quot;:

1. Filter to RED items only. Do NOT re-display GREEN or YELLOW items.
2. For each RED, present:
   - The requirement text (truncated to first sentence if long)
   - Why Salesforce cannot meet it (from Response_Flag_Reason__c)
   - Whether it is negotiable or a hard no:
     * Hard no: dedicated hardware, on-premises, source code escrow, IL6, customer VMs, customer-specific NDAs, SBOMs, SecNumCloud, classified data, IPv6, ISO 20000/14001/45001, defer upgrades, customer approval before changes, encryption in memory
     * Negotiable: service credits (legal can discuss), resolution times (Premier/Signature tiers), right to audit (contract terms), breach notification timing (DSR negotiation), background checks (Gov Cloud option), on-site audits (contract terms)
   - Recommended next step:
     * Hard no: &quot;Flag for SE review — recommend alternative language or take exception&quot;
     * Negotiable: &quot;Engage legal/AE — this may be addressable through contract negotiation or product add-on&quot;
3. End with a deal risk summary:
   - Total RED count
   - How many are hard nos vs negotiable
   - Recommended action: e.g. &quot;3 hard nos and 2 negotiable items. Recommend SE review before responding. The negotiable items may be resolvable with legal engagement.&quot;

YELLOW FLAG DISTINCTION:
Yellow flags come in two types:
- BINARY_CAN_DIFFERENTLY (ruleId is NOT &apos;NO_MATCH&apos;): Salesforce meets the intent but not the letter. These have a pre-written alternative explanation in Response_Flag_Reason__c. Present these as &quot;Partially met&quot; with the alternative.
- NO_MATCH (ruleId = &apos;NO_MATCH&apos;): No rule matched. These need AI-generated answers from Knowledge retrieval. Present these as &quot;Needs research&quot; and offer to generate answers.

When the user asks about yellows, distinguish between these two types.</description>
